 Rafael Mariano Grossi, Director General of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), speaks during a press conference in Vienna, Austria, Dec 17, 2021. IAEA Director General Rafael Mariano Grossi held a press conference on Friday to brief journalists about developments related to the IAEA's monitoring and verification work in Iran. The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) will soon install new surveillance cameras at Iran's Karaj nuclear facility under an agreement between the two sides, the international nuclear energy watchdog said on Wednesday. (Xinhua/Guo Chen)  Rafael Mariano Grossi, Director General of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), displays a surveillance camera during a press conference in Vienna, Austria, Dec 17, 2021. IAEA Director General Rafael Mariano Grossi held a press conference on Friday to brief journalists about developments related to the IAEA's monitoring and verification work in Iran. The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) will soon install new surveillance cameras at Iran's Karaj nuclear facility under an agreement between the two sides, the international nuclear energy watchdog said on Wednesday. (Xinhua/Guo Chen)  Rafael Mariano Grossi, Director General of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), speaks during a press conference in Vienna, Austria, Dec 17, 2021. IAEA Director General Rafael Mariano Grossi held a press conference on Friday to brief journalists about developments related to the IAEA's monitoring and verification work in Iran. The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) will soon install new surveillance cameras at Iran's Karaj nuclear facility under an agreement between the two sides, the international nuclear energy watchdog said on Wednesday. (Xinhua/Guo Chen)  Rafael Mariano Grossi, Director General of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), speaks during a press conference in Vienna, Austria, Dec 17, 2021. IAEA Director General Rafael Mariano Grossi held a press conference o